# ============================================================
# CRITICAL: this is what actually keeps your repo safe.
# The Firebase config inside index.html is NOT a secret and is safe
# to commit — it's meant to be public. The files below ARE secrets.
# If any of these ever get committed, rotate them immediately in the
# Firebase Console (Service Accounts → Generate new key, then delete
# the old one) even after removing them from git history, since old
# commits can still be found in git history/forks.
# ============================================================

# Firebase service account keys — full admin access to your project
*serviceAccountKey*.json
*firebase-adminsdk*.json
viadice-service-account.json

# Node
node_modules/
npm-debug.log

# Environment files, if you add any later
.env
.env.local